annotation.TEXT: Alright, as usual, let's begin by looking at the map and stuff...
So, it looks like we are goin' to da MOON!!!

Alright, I'll be resuming the Roadtrip to the Moon next time! If I made any mistakes while rattling off all those elements, or if elements 119 or 120 ever get an official name, let me know! To be continued...
Just carefully tap myself into position...
I really hope this doesn't take me so many tries that I hit the end of the known Periodic Table...
YES!!! Now, please don't screw this up...
Oh, man. That looks really tricky... (And there's a reason that I'm mentioning Periodic Table elements now.)
Whew! Okay, I'm glad that's over! I could definitely use a break now.
Pfft... Well, at least I stubbed my toe there AFTER reaching the checkpoint!
That's one of the three trinkets already.
Geez, I've already spent over half the video here so far! This really is getting ridiculous!

Alright, there's an arrow pointing to the right, but it doesn't look like I'll be able to go to the right from here (well, unless the ceiling spikes stop early enough in the room to the right). I guess I'm going left for now.
Ow, they're larger than they appear!

Aw, I was hoping for a checkpoint that wasn't on the other side of a one-way passage like that... Well, I still want to take the hard route, which I think is necessary for that trinket that I badly want.
There really needs to be a checkpoint here, honestly.
We're on the Periodic Table's home stretch now!
Ow, my blue ring of death!
That is kind of a tight squeeze there, and I have to be careful not to overshoot once I get through.
D'oh! I let off the right arrow key just a tad too soon there.
Ah, now I can go to the right from here.
Ah, the ceiling spikes did end early enough here for me to have gone this way immediately, but I would've missed the first trinket if I had done that.
Only one crewmate and three trinkets to find, though.
Woo! First try there! But, I'll have to do it again here!

Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV! Here are the voting results this time: 2 votes to save Golden Spiral for last (counts as votes for the other levels), 2 votes for Golden Spiral, 5 votes for Line Wrap, and 7 votes for Roadtrip to the Moon!

Yeah, we're going on 11 minutes now, and... Wow, those deaths... And, as you could perhaps tell from the Periodic Table of Elements that I rattled off over the course of the video (assuming I didn't make a mistake), 120 of those deaths occurred between when I saw the second trinket and when I collected it!
Yep, I parked my Viridian there alright. Also, as I suspected, I do indeed have to go through the hard path of Diverging Streets in order to reach that trinket that I badly want.
Hmm... A choice of two paths. Well, let's take a peek at what's to the right first...
Finally landed on it! The level of precision required there is kind of ridiculous!
Aha! My instinct was right! This detour was totally worth it!
Alright, I want to check something real quick over here. I'm going to avoid the Easy Street checkpoint and see what's above that room.
Argh, I think this is more demanding than Veni Vidi Vici! And there are only two screens involved here!
Very good! Okay, now for more of the same up there...
Yes, I'll definitely want that, but I'm going to have to approach that room from a different direction in order to even make an attempt at it.
Dang it! I so had it there, but I somehow managed to overshoot by that much!
Come on, don't get careless now.
I think it's been over ten minutes anyway.
Argh! I've gotta aim for the left lane there.
But, I made it on the next try! Oh, my god! That was insane! And, I'm not even done yet! But, at least I get checkpoints in the trinket's room!
But, I guess if there was a checkpoint there, you guys wouldn't be learning the Periodic Table right now.
Ow, Viridian tried to learn TM35 Flamethrower, but failed!
This map's pretty big. Looks like it's around 10x10. This may take a few episodes.
Oh, I didn't realize that the game was gonna finish the "Objects in mirror..." sentence here.
Oh, god. I just noticed that I'll have to pull off two tight squeezes in a row here before reaching the next checkpoint, and then again just before the trinket!
Okay, okay! Don't screw up this time, even after I get the trinket, because I still have to get out of here!
Alright, now the next few flips aren't actually that tough. I just have to be careful not to overshoot while lining up for them.
And, can I reach the next checkpoint without screwing up?
Wow, that's kind of nutters. That platform is almost entirely in the spiky wall when I get to it, so I've gotta land on the very edge of its right side.
Ugh! It takes so many tries just to get that far...
Yes, I'm going to continue the Periodic Table deaths here.
I'm surprised I got past that roadblock so easily. So, what horrors await me next?
There's totally gotta be something over to the right there.
And of course, this means even more ridiculous precision...
